1
00:01:29,050 --> 00:01:32,020
[Silent Honor]

2
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:34,979
[Episode 12]

3
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,440
Mrs. Chen was quick to react.

4
00:02:37,579 --> 00:02:40,710
It would've been terrible
if she had gotten into the car.

5
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:44,480
Seems she does have
some experience in this after all.

6
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:49,260
What's wrong?

7
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:51,790
I'm still a bit worried.

8
00:02:52,430 --> 00:02:53,510
Earlier at the teahouse,

9
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:55,420
she was planning to
take the note with the address

10
00:02:55,420 --> 00:02:56,750
and come straight here.

11
00:02:58,740 --> 00:02:59,460
Go quickly.

12
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:00,990
Follow her by car

13
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:04,700
and escort her home—
as long as it can be done safely.

14
00:03:04,710 --> 00:03:05,300
Okay.

15
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:12,670
Why are we operating so early today?

16
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:14,840
We've been arresting people every night,

17
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:16,350
[Weng Lianwang, member of the
Counterintelligence Section of the BIS]

18
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,220
and now people in Taipei
have gotten smart.

19
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,910
They don't even leave their homes anymore.

20
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,640
So, we wanna try during the day.

21
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:21,950
Weng Lianwang.

22
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:24,460
I heard the Director was looking for
someone from your team,

23
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,860
that Operation Captain,

24
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:26,970
Yu something...

25
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,310
Yu Xiaonan.

26
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:30,940
Right.

27
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,570
He wanted to talk to him.

28
00:03:32,770 --> 00:03:34,520
Is it that your team leader Gu
won't be able to come back

29
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,579
and they want him to take over?

30
00:03:35,579 --> 00:03:37,240
Why don't you team up with him?

31
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:39,810
He's not a local.

32
00:03:40,170 --> 00:03:42,740
He's not like you, Lianwang.
You speak Mandarin.

33
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:44,740
With his clumsy way of speaking,

34
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:48,079
he can't even check IDs properly.

35
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:50,380
And he wants to be a team leader?

36
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:54,230
Get to work now, hurry up.

37
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,610
Get in, quickly!

38
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,100
Take out your ID.

39
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:26,940
Wait a moment!

40
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:27,500
Ricksh…

41
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:32,800
Officer, what's the matter?

42
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,860
We're from the BIS. Show me your ID.

43
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,030
Alright.

44
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:39,230
This is my pass.

45
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:46,090
There's something wrong with your ID.

46
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,210
Let's go to the bureau to verify it.

47
00:04:48,210 --> 00:04:50,220
I have a family member in
the Provincial Police Department.

48
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:52,090
This pass was just newly issued to me.

49
00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:53,300
Let's go to the bureau to verify it.

50
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,250
Then everything will be clear,

51
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,180
don't you think?

52
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,800
Take her away!

53
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:59,610
Why are you grabbing my purse?

54
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:01,230
Wait, what are you doing?

55
00:05:01,230 --> 00:05:01,780
Move it!

56
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:02,750
It's new!

57
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:03,980
I just got it!

58
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:04,570
Shut up!

59
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:11,830
Help!

60
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,480
The BIS is arresting innocent people!

61
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,940
I'm a professor
at National Taiwan University!

62
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,740
I'll report you to President Fu!

63
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:20,040
I'm a professor
at National Taiwan University!

64
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:22,070
I'll report you to President Fu!

65
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:22,810
Behave yourself!

66
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:23,370
Get in!

67
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:24,250
Get in!

68
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,360
Mrs. Chen hadn't been followed

69
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,360
from the time she left the teahouse.

70
00:05:38,690 --> 00:05:39,630
And those agents

71
00:05:39,650 --> 00:05:41,480
were originally hiding in the car.

72
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:44,550
They only started checking and searching
when they saw people coming out.

73
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:46,130
They pretended to be catching Communists,

74
00:05:46,130 --> 00:05:48,130
but they were actually just checking IDs.

75
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:49,190
And they specifically targeted

76
00:05:49,190 --> 00:05:50,790
people who looked well-off.

77
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,409
So, I think

78
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,770
it's more like a kidnapping for ransom.

79
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:56,490
They won't take her to the BIS.

80
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:59,950
They'll definitely hold her somewhere else
and demand money.

81
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:01,320
Looking at it this way,

82
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:02,500
I think...

83
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:05,310
Mrs. Chen's identity
is probably still safe.

84
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:07,570
What I'm worried about now
is whether the film that she has

85
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:08,630
has been destroyed or not.

86
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:10,160
Time is of the essence now.

87
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,770
The sooner we rescue her,

88
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:14,880
the less risk of exposure there is.

89
00:06:15,450 --> 00:06:17,690
If it's really kidnapping and blackmail,

90
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:18,880
is it possible

91
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:21,010
to find a suitable person

92
00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:22,570
to redeem her?

93
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,920
The problem is

94
00:06:24,450 --> 00:06:25,950
finding the right person.

95
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,920
Who can step forward now?

96
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:30,430
Director Duan.

97
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:31,180
What?

98
00:06:31,330 --> 00:06:32,190
Director Duan.

99
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:36,260
Once Duan Tuizhi gets involved,

100
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:37,950
the story Mrs. Chen fabricated earlier

101
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:38,880
will fall apart.

102
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:41,310
They arrested several people at that time.

103
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,640
Do you know anyone else?

104
00:06:43,690 --> 00:06:44,370
No.

105
00:06:46,690 --> 00:06:48,120
There is one person though.

106
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,950
He claimed to be a professor
at National Taiwan University.

107
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:53,159
He kept shouting
the BIS was arresting innocent people.

108
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:55,570
He threatened to report them
to President Fool.

109
00:06:55,570 --> 00:06:57,170
What's that President Fool?

110
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,250
Not Fool.

111
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:03,360
He should be referring to Fu Sinian,
President of National Taiwan University.

112
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,120
Fu the Cannon, right?

113
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:04,800
Yes.

114
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,320
If he finds out

115
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:09,620
that a professor from his university
has been kidnapped by the BIS,

116
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,190
he would dare to storm Caoshan Villa

117
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:12,720
and pound on Chiang's desk.

118
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:14,340
Perfect!

119
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:16,490
The key now is

120
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,450
how to contact President Fu.

121
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,280
I'll figure something out.

122
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:27,860
I've been with
the Counterintelligence Section

123
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:29,260
for about half a year now.

124
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:32,860
The Communist spies I've seen—

125
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:34,370
if we count them on our fingers and toes,

126
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,630
we'd run out of digits.

127
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:37,890
Not a single one of them

128
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:40,630
has remained silent
after our leader interrogated them.

129
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:41,870
I just don't buy it!

130
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:44,290
Believe me!

131
00:07:46,810 --> 00:07:49,070
Some of them, without certain measures,

132
00:07:49,190 --> 00:07:50,390
would not cooperate.

133
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:52,250
Like this one.

134
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:53,950
Him.

135
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:55,690
Come on.

136
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:56,690
You...

137
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:58,860
Take it off.

138
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,120
Off!

139
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:08,370
Xuecheng!

140
00:08:09,190 --> 00:08:09,850
Jiancheng!

141
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:10,870
Where are you?

142
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:16,680
You two are cheating!

143
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:21,370
You can't lift that up!

144
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:24,950
Got you!

145
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,520
I'm going to tickle you!

146
00:08:31,690 --> 00:08:32,610
You're cheating!

147
00:08:32,610 --> 00:08:33,770
Whose turn is it now?

148
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:35,770
Let him catch us first.

149
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:37,000
Jiancheng, it's your turn.

150
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:37,370
Alright.

151
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:38,700
You try to catch us both.

152
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,510
Okay.

153
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,750
Okay.

154
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,700
It's not tight enough. Wait a moment.

155
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,760
Come on, Xuecheng, help him put it on.

156
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:51,890
No peeking!

157
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,450
No peeking, you hear me?

158
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,270
Hurry up!

159
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:05,630
Everyone, listen up!

160
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:09,630
There are problems with
all your identification documents.

161
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,700
Your identities cannot be confirmed.

162
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,500
If we follow legal procedures,

163
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:15,740
you'd be locked here
for at least 10 days to 2 weeks.

164
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:17,940
So, I've come up with a solution for you.

165
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:19,390
Right now,

166
00:09:19,630 --> 00:09:21,390
you can take your new ID and go home.

167
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:24,190
It doesn't cost much—
just 200 New Taiwan Dollars.

168
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:26,410
Those who don't have enough cash

169
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,500
can call your family to bring it over.

170
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,520
You, come out.

171
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:41,390
I'm talking to you.

172
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,140
Not you, you.

173
00:09:44,170 --> 00:09:44,970
I understand.

174
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,280
Mr. Liu.

175
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:50,560
I have something to attend to.
I'll be off.

176
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:50,950
Okay.

177
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,730
What are you eating?

178
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:58,360
See you later.

179
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:02,710
Move!

180
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,920
Have you decided?

181
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:20,930
Do you want to pay the supplementary fee?

182
00:10:21,330 --> 00:10:23,440
If you pay in US dollars or gold,

183
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:24,680
I'll give you a 10% discount.

184
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,120
Actually, my son-in-law is your colleague,

185
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,480
Wang Changcheng
from the Police Department.

186
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:32,610
Why don't you make a call to confirm?

187
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:34,390
From our sister department?

188
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:35,450
Yes, that's right.

189
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,900
Why didn't you say so earlier?

190
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:40,820
I would have processed yours first.

191
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:47,580
Connect me to the Telecommunications
Office, Provincial Police Department.

192
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:48,840
Okay.

193
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:53,530
Hello, is Wang Changcheng there?

194
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:56,130
I'd like to speak with Wang Changcheng.

195
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:57,460
I'm his mother-in-law.

196
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:00,150
What? He's not there?

197
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:02,010
Where did he go?

198
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,700
Can you give me a phone number?

199
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,290
Okay, thank you.

200
00:11:07,570 --> 00:11:09,220
If you can't get through, don't bother.

201
00:11:09,220 --> 00:11:10,420
Those who work in telecommunications

202
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:12,820
would put on headphones
and work all night.

203
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,730
Arrange a private room for her.

204
00:11:14,730 --> 00:11:17,130
Let her get some rest.
Call again tomorrow.

205
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:18,500
Officer.

206
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:20,730
Please let me make a call home.

207
00:11:20,830 --> 00:11:21,780
Thank you.

208
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,360
If you can't get through, forget it.

209
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,520
Take her upstairs.

210
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,400
Let me try one more time.

211
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,700
Let me check again.

212
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,320
I'm hungry.

213
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:19,980
I've been detained for too long.

214
00:12:20,570 --> 00:12:22,290
I don't even know how long

215
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:23,930
you're going to keep me here.

216
00:12:24,770 --> 00:12:26,630
My son-in-law is your colleague.

217
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:29,060
Just give me a little help, Officer.

218
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,120
Thank you.

219
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:40,510
I'll just take a little more.

220
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:42,480
Thank you. Thanks.

221
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,220
Go.

222
00:12:44,370 --> 00:12:45,500
Thank you, Officer.

223
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:56,950
Thank you.

224
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,790
If something unexpected happens,

225
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:51,740
pull the film out from here
and it will be exposed.

226
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:19,980
So you finally decided to come home!

227
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:20,930
I was working overtime.

228
00:14:20,930 --> 00:14:22,740
Mom still hasn't come home!

229
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,120
I heard from the neighbors that

230
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,770
the BIS has been arresting people
everywhere these days.

231
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:28,050
I'm worried something happened to her,

232
00:14:28,050 --> 00:14:30,170
but I didn't dare leave the child
home alone to go look for her,

233
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:32,040
so I was waiting for you to come home
before searching.

234
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,580
Who'd thought
you'd be working overtime again today!

235
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:34,700
You should have called me.

236
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,100
The phone at home is broken!

237
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:36,910
Broken?

238
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:39,100
I'm worried sick!

239
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:39,910
Don't worry.

240
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:41,860
Mom didn't say where she was going?

241
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,100
She just said she was going shopping

242
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:44,560
but didn't mention where.

243
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,700
The phone line might be down.

244
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:50,160
You don't think
Mom ran into the BIS agents, do you?

245
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:54,480
All the big shots are in Chongqing lately.

246
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:57,080
I haven't heard of any operations.

247
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,200
Why don't you ask your old colleagues

248
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,200
at the BIS about it?

249
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,600
Can't do that.

250
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,790
Why not?

251
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:08,080
First, there aren't
any operations going on.

252
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,410
As long as Mom isn't arrested,

253
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:11,580
she's not in any danger.

254
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:14,120
She probably just visited an old friend

255
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,330
and lost track of time.

256
00:15:15,330 --> 00:15:17,190
She might have tried to call home,

257
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:18,820
but the phone line was down.

258
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:20,640
You know, what if

259
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:22,410
nothing actully happened?

260
00:15:22,410 --> 00:15:23,670
If I start asking around,

261
00:15:23,670 --> 00:15:25,470
people might get suspicious

262
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,840
and think we have connections
with Communist spies.

263
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,650
That wouldn't be good.

264
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:30,220
At a time like this,

265
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:32,600
you're still worried about
what others might think?

266
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,790
Mom cares about me.

267
00:15:33,790 --> 00:15:35,410
She came all the way from Hong Kong

268
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:36,990
to take care of me and the child.

269
00:15:36,990 --> 00:15:38,970
Afraid of being a burden,

270
00:15:38,990 --> 00:15:40,540
she constantly contributes
to our household expenses

271
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,600
and helps you make money in business.

272
00:15:43,650 --> 00:15:45,580
Now, she might be in danger,

273
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:47,250
and you won't even ask your colleagues?

274
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,360
It's just one simple question.

275
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,290
Would it kill you?

276
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:50,360
Keep your voice down.

277
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,320
Mom pays for all our groceries.

278
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,820
You haven't missed a single meal!

279
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,460
Enough! Lower your voice!

280
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,800
The neighbors are all my colleagues.

281
